<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>FixMyStreet – Down for maintenance</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Source+Sans+Pro:400,600" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <style>
      html {
        -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;
        -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1em 4em 1em;
        max-width: 28em;
        font-family: "Source Sans Pro", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        color: #222;
        background-color: #fff;
      }

      a { color: #222; }
      a:focus, a:hover { background-color: #ffd000; }

      a.logo {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 16px 0;
        background-color: #fff;
      }

      img {
        border: none;
      }

      h1 {
        border-top: solid 8px #ffd000;
        border-bottom: solid 8px #ffd000;
        font-size: 3em;
        line-height: 1em;
        margin: 1em -1em 0.5em -1em;
        padding: 0.2em 1em;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      p {
        font-size: 21px;
        line-height: 1.4em;
        margin: 1em 0 0 0;
      }

      @media(min-width: 30em){
        h1 {
          font-size: 4em;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <a href="https://www.societyworks.org" class="logo">
        <img width="220" height="46" alt="SocietyWorks" src="data:image/png;base64,">
    </a>
    <h1>Site temporarily unavailable</h1>
    <p>If you’re seeing this message, it’s very likely that we’re performing a spot of maintenance.
    Please check back in a few minutes and everything should be in order.</p>
    <p>For more up-to-date information about what’s happening, please <a href="https://status.societyworks.org/">see our status page</a>.</p>
    <p>In the meantime, thanks for your patience.</p>
  </body>
</html>
